[h1]The font-weight Property[/h1]

The font-weight controls the boldness or thickness of the text. The values can be set as [b]normal[/b] (default size), [b]bold[/b], [b]bolder[/b], and [b]lighter[/b].

[b]The HTML:[/b] [code format="html" ]<p class="light">This is a font with a "lighter" weight.</p>
<p class="bold">This is a font with a "bold" weight.</p>
<p class="bolder">This is a font with a "bolder" weight.</p>[/code]
[b]The CSS:[/b] [code format="css" codeId="516"]p.light {   
   font-weight: [b]lighter[/b];
}
p.bold {   
   font-weight: [b]bold[/b];
}
p.bolder {
   font-weight: [b]bolder[/b];
}[/code]
[b]Result: [/b][img id="2592" width="100%"]

[h1]The font-weight Property[/h1]

You can also define the font weight with a number from [b]100[/b] (thin) to [b]900[/b] (thick), according to how thick you want the text to be. 
400 is the same as normal, and 700 is the same as bold. 

[b]The HTML:[/b] [code format="html" ]<p class="light">This is a font with a "lighter" weight.</p>
<p class="thick">This is a font with a "bold" weight.</p>
<p class="thicker">This is a font with a "700" weight.</p>[/code]
[b]The CSS:[/b] [code format="css" codeId="517"]p.light {
   font-weight: [b]lighter[/b];
}
p.thick {
   font-weight: [b]bold[/b];
}
p.thicker {
   font-weight: [b]700[/b];
}[/code]
[b]Result: [/b][img id="2593" width="100%"]
[note]The HTML [b]<strong>[/b] tag also makes the text [b]bold[/b].[/note]
